i SPY 106 The Loser (10/20/1965)

Scott is abducted by the drug dealer Ramon and his thugs and held in a back room of a seedy nightclub in the New Territories. Here he meets Angel, the world-weary, opium-addicted chanteuse who becomes a pawn in a life-and-death game of wits between Scott and Ramon. 
The Loser is the episode that is required viewing for anyone who wonders why Bill Cosby earned an Emmy for I Spy&#039;s first season. Some credit should go to Robert Culp -- this is one of the best of his seven scripts. Eartha Kitt earned an Emmy nomination of her own for her portrayal of a truly lost soul.
